I"^<h1 id="news">News</h1>

<p><br /><strong>22. Apr 2024</strong></p>
<p>Xu-Cheng He gave an invited seminar at the <a href="https://www.solas-int.org/events/solas-seminar/solas-semianr-viii.html">SOLAS open seminar</a></p>

<p><br /><strong>05. May 2023</strong></p>
<p>Xu-Cheng He was invited to participate the Atmospheric Chemistry Colloquium for Emerging Senior Scientists (ACCESS XVII).</p>

<p><br /><strong>12. Jan 2023</strong></p>
<p>Xu-Cheng He co-chairs the ‘Measurement and modeling of atmospheric cloud condensation nuclei and related chemistry’ session at AMS2023.</p>

<p><br /><strong>4. Jan 2023</strong></p>
<p>Xu-Cheng He starts visiting the Centre for Atmospheric Science, University of Cambridge. He will work on simulating atmospheric aerosol formation processes using the UKUM model with Luke Abraham and Alex Archibald.</p>

<p><br /><strong>10. Sep 2022</strong></p>
<p>Xu-Cheng He joins the CLOUD15 experiments. He is leading the experimental programs investigating marine particle formation processes.</p>

<p><br /><strong>06. Sep 2022</strong></p>
<p>Xu-Cheng He wins the Extraordinary Potential Prize of Chinese Government Award for Outstanding Self-financed Students Abroad as one of the 20 awardees globally.</p>

<p><br /><strong>05. Sep 2022</strong></p>
<p>Xu-Cheng He gives a talk titled ‘Critical role of HIO2 in iodine oxoacid nucleation’ at the International Aerosol Conference, Athens, 2022.</p>

<p><br /><strong>01. Sep 2022</strong></p>
<p>Xu-Cheng He joins Finnish Meteorological Institute as a post-doctoral researcher.</p>

<p><br /><strong>10. Aug 2022</strong></p>
<p>Xu-Cheng He gives an invited talk at the Gordon Research Conference for molecular and ionic clusters.</p>

<p><br /><strong>05. May 2022</strong></p>
<p>Xu-Cheng He wins the PhD dissertation award from University of Helsinki (4/500).</p>

<p><br /><strong>01. Mar 2022</strong></p>
<p>Xu-Cheng He joins <a href="https://engineering.cmu.edu/accelerator/research/faculty/gordon-group.html">Gordon Group</a> at Carnegie Mellon University for 6 months as a visiting researcher, including one-month’s model training.</p>

